  "local_port": 54722,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which library is better than the BGI library(graphics.h) for graphics in C++?",
  "response": "If you are looking for more modern and versatile alternatives to the BGI library (`graphics.h`) for graphics programming in C++, there are several options that provide more features, better performance, and support for contemporary graphics programming practices:\n\n1. **SFML (Simple and Fast Multimedia Library):** \n   - SFML is an easy-to-use library, great for 2D graphics, sound, and handling input.\n   - It is well-documented and supports modern C++.\n   - Platforms: Windows, Linux, macOS.\n\n2. **SDL (Simple DirectMedia Layer):**\n   - SDL provides low-level access to audio, keyboard, mouse, joystick, and graphics hardware.\n   - It's commonly used for game development and supports both 2D and 3D graphics.\n   - Platforms: Windows, Linux, macOS, Android, iOS.\n\n3. **OpenGL:**\n   - A powerful, low-level API that is widely used for both 2D and 3D graphics.\n   - Provides great flexibility and control over the GPU, but requires more setup and learning.\n   - Platforms: Cross-platform.\n\n4. **Allegro:**\n   - Allegro is a library specifically designed for video game development.\n   - It supports graphics, audio, input, and even has support for a game GUI.\n   - Platforms: Windows, Linux, macOS.\n\n5. **Qt:**\n   - Primarily known as a GUI toolkit, but also provides powerful 2D and 3D graphics capabilities.\n   - It is suitable for applications that need a rich user interface along with graphics.\n   - Platforms: Windows, Linux, macOS, Android, iOS.\n\n6. **DirectX:**\n   - A collection of APIs from Microsoft for handling tasks related to multimedia, especially game programming and video, on Microsoft platforms.\n   - It provides extensive 3D graphics capabilities but is Windows-exclusive.\n\n7. **Vulkan:**\n   - A modern, high-performance 3D graphics API that provides more direct control over GPU and lower overhead than OpenGL.\n   - It is more complex to learn but offers high efficiency and cross-platform capabilities.\n\nThese libraries are actively maintained and provide a wide range of functionalities that better meet the demands of modern graphics programming compared to the outdated BGI library. When choosing a library, consider the specific needs of your project, such as ease of use, performance requirements, and platform support.",
